{
  "stem": "10406.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The younger generation already dressed in a modern way with suits and ties and were-- and didn't have any [? payot ?] anymore and didn't wear beards.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents owned a store that sold material for suits, and coats, and dresses, like a garment type of business.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother-- my mother worked in the store.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My brother and sister went to school, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, on that market day, which I believe was-- it was either Wednesday or Thursday, it would get very crowded, a lot of customers.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then my mother would ask us to come and help, like just to be in the store to make sure that-- you know, cause the shelves were open, people don't take things and walk out.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It-- I would say the center of the town and going outside towards the suburbs a little bit was mostly Jewish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then starting from there, the farms would start already.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it would be people that live in town but actually have land outside of the city and-- but they would have their livestock in-- in-- in the-- in the [?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "CLO-- ?] in that area, in the barns.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that would start already being non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that would be mostly Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because that area of Poland was-- was considered the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I would say 80% of the population was Ukrainian Orthodox-- Russian or Ukrainian Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And about 10% of the population was Polish Catholic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then 10% of the overall population was 10% Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But in this particular town, probably 60% to 70% of the population was Jewish because all the crafts were concentrated there and the stores were concentrated in town.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the Jews lived in that area.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
